description: TEHRAN – Iran’s military went after terrorists responsible for the deaths of 10 soldiers and police officers in Sistan and Balouchestan, as the province’s governor declared a day of morning on Sunday.
title: Iran mourns terror victims, targets suspects in retaliation

description: TEHRAN – A civilian casualty has been reported in the aftermath of recent Israeli airstrikes against Iran, which occurred in the early hours of Saturday.
title: Civilian pronounced dead after Israeli airstrikes on Iran raising number of martyrs to five

description: TEHRAN - Kayhan devoted its editorial to Israel's Saturday morning attack on Iran.
title: Wait for the response

description: TEHRAN – Over 60 professors and academics from Iran's prestigious Sharif University of Technology have condemned a year of brutal Israeli violence in Gaza and Lebanon, simultaneously criticizing the West's deafening silence and inaction as a glaring display of hypocrisy.

description: TEHRAN – The city of Shiraz witnessed a solemn gathering on Sunday as the funeral procession for martyr Masoumeh Karbasi began at Shohada Square in the Iranian city of Shiraz.
title: Thousands gather in Shiraz for funeral of Iranian woman martyred in Lebanon

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s Foreign Minister has issued a strong condemnation of recent Israeli actions, urging swift action to mitigate a growing threat to peace and stability in the region.
title: Araghchi calls for UN action against dangerous escalation of Israeli aggression

description: TEHRAN – Multiple Iranian officials have asserted Iran's right to respond to Israel’s Saturday attack on the West Asian country’s soil, as the nation mourns the loss of four soldiers who died in fending off the regime’s airstrikes.
title: Officials say Iran will respond to Israel’s attack as public demand for retaliation grows

description: TEHRAN – The Israeli regime invaded the territory of Iran on Saturday. Iran’s air defense system was targeted through this aggressive military attack. Responding to this act of aggression is Iran's inherent defense right.

description: TEHRAN - At the end of his speech on Sunday with the families of the martyrs of security, Ayatollah Ali Khamenei pointed to Israel’s pre-dawn attack on Iran on Saturday. Although his remarks were brief, they carried great significance as his first reaction following the assault on Iran.
title: Iran owes security to his wisdom

description: TEHRAN – Sepahan and Foolad football teams shared the spoils in a 2-2 draw on Matchweek 9 of 2024/25 Iran’s Persian Gulf Professional League (PGPL) on Sunday.
title: Sepahan, Foolad share the spoils: PGPL

description: TEHRAN – Iran defeated Jordan 4-2 to conclude their AFC U17 Asian Cup Saudi Arabia 2025 Qualifiers Group A campaign on Sunday.
title: Iran defeat Jordan at AFC U17 Asian Cup 2025 qualifier

description: TEHRAN – The Iranian embassy in Belgium has categorically dismissed the European Union's unfounded assertion regarding Iran's alleged involvement in the Ukraine conflict.
title: Iran rejects EU accusations of involvement in Ukraine conflict

description: TEHRAN- A representative of the Jewish community in the Iranian parliament has urged Iran to respond swiftly and decisively to the recent attack by the Zionist regime.
title: Jewish MP urges swift Iranian response to Zionist aggression

description: TEHRAN – The Iranian Embassy in London has expressed its disapproval of the British Prime Minister's position regarding the recent aggressive actions taken by the Israeli regime against Iran, labeling it as inconsistent with international law and the principles outlined in the UN Charter.
title: Iran rebukes UK PM's stance on Israeli aggression

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s vice president in strategic affairs emphasized Iran's determination to stand firm against all enemies and defend its sovereignty, even in the face of potential Israeli military retaliation.

title: Hezbollah kills 4 Israeli soldiers, injures over 60

description: TEHRAN- The weekend’s deadly truck-ramming attack in Israel appears to be the tip of the iceberg for the regime in the wake of growing resentment against its atrocities in Gaza and Lebanon.
title: Tel Aviv truck-ramming: Israel given a taste of its own medicine

description: TEHRAN- The Israeli carnage in northern Gaza shows no signs of abating more than three weeks after the occupying regime launched a new brutal offensive there.
title: Israel turns north Gaza into death zone

description: TEHRAN - The people in the only country that has been hit by nuclear bombs, namely Japan, are getting more and more angry at the Israeli regime’s genocidal war on the Palestinians in the Gaza Strip.
title: Japan stands with Palestine

description: BEIRUT - On the eve of the unprecedented attacks on Israel’s Merkava tanks by Hezbollah, the Axis of Resistance’s peoples have literally received the “Israeli retaliation” on Iran with mockery and disdain.

description: TEHRAN-Mehrab Theater in Tehran hosted the first performance of the play “Out at Sea” written by Polish dramatis Slawomir Mrozek on October 27 and will continue staging the play until November 15.
title: Slawomir Mrozek’s “Out at Sea” on Mehrab Theater stage

description: TEHRAN- Six international groups from Uzbekistan, Armenia, Iraq, Brazil, Turkey, and Russia are set to perform at the 29th edition of Iran’s International Theater Festival for Children and Young Adults, the secretary of the festival announced during a press conference in Tehran on Sunday.
title: Iran’s children’s theater festival to welcome performers from six countries

description: TEHRAN-The group exhibition “The Storm of Art” was launched on Sunday at the Palestine Museum of Contemporary Art in Tehran.
title: “Storm of Art” exhibition launched at Palestine Museum of Contemporary Art

description: TEHRAN - Maymand, a UNESCO World Heritage site in Iran's southern Kerman province, has undergone improvements with cobblestone paving along sections of its touristic routes.
title: Cobblestone paths to enhance tourism experience in UNESCO-listed Maymand

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s Cultural Attaché to Turkmenistan has said that historical and religious bonds serve as the backbone of tourism ties among the two neighboring countries.
title: Iranian cultural attaché highlights tourism ties with Turkmenistan

description: TEHRAN – The tourism chief of Isfahan province has announced plans to transform Qale Narin, an ancient mud-brick fortress in Nain county, into a site museum, aiming to highlight the region’s rich history and attract more tourism.
title: Narin fortress in Isfahan to become a site museum

description: TEHRAN - The International Volleyball Hall of Fame welcomed its 2024 Class of Inductees on October 19 in Holyoke, Massachusetts. Among the nine honored were individuals who have profoundly influenced sitting volleyball, including Iran’s Hadi Rezaei and the United States’ John Kessel and the late Bill Kauffman, whose achievements in coaching, development and communications have helped elevate the sport on the global stage.
title: International Volleyball Hall of Fame honors Rezaei

description: TEHRAN – The bazaar of Fuman, located in the ancient city of the same name in the northern Gilan province, is a vibrant marketplace that reflects the lifestyle, traditions, and customs of the local people.
title: Bazaar of Fuman: a lively reflection of tradition in Gilan

description: TEHRAN –A total of 1056 Iranian researchers have been recognized among the world’s top one percent most-cited researchers in 2024, indicating a 12 percent increase compared to 938 identified researchers in 2023, the head of the Islamic World Science Citation (ISC) Institute has said.
title: Over 1,000 Iranians among world's 1% most-cited researchers

description: TEHRAN –The head of the Iranian Red Crescent Society (IRCS), Pirhossein Kolivand, has held separate meetings with the president of the Emirates Red Crescent, Hamdan bin Zayed, and the president of the German Red Cross, Gerda Hasselfeldt.
title: IRCS to boost co-op with German Red Cross, Emirates Red Crescent

description: TEHRAN -In an effort to enhance the capacity of the health ministry to address the prevalence of malaria in southeastern regions, the World Health Organization (WHO) in cooperation with the Government of Japan has procured 50,000 malaria rapid diagnostic tests as well as 4,902 mosquito dome tents.
title: WHO, Japan further support Iran in eradicating malaria

description: MADRID – In the early hours of Saturday, several explosions were heard in Tehran, the capital of Iran. Various local media reported that residents in the western part of the city heard these blasts. Iranian official sources indicated that military bases in the west and southwest of Tehran were targeted in an Israeli attack. Additionally, sounds related to air defense fire were reported.
title: Limited and ineffective: Israel's attacks on Iran under scrutiny

description: TEHRAN- Ian’s export to Tajikistan has risen 33 percent in the first half of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-September 21), as compared to the same period of time in the past year, the vice chairman of Iran-Tajikistan Joint Economic Committee stated.
title: Iran’s export to Tajikistan increases 33% in H1

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s saffron production is expected to reach about 400 tons in the current Iranian calendar year (ends in late March 2025), Hossein Zeynali, the director of Agriculture Ministry’s medicinal plants national plan, announced.
title: Annual saffron production expected to reach 400 tons

description: TEHRAN - The value of Iran’s exports to the members of the Organization of Islamic Conference (OIC) increased by 22 percent in the first seven months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-October 21), the Islamic Republic of Iran Customs Administration (IRICA) announced.
title: Iran’s exports to OIC member states rises 22%

description: TEHRAN – Iran Chamber of Commerce, Industries, Mines and Agriculture held the second National Economic Security Conference on Sunday in collaboration with Economic Security Police of Iran, the ICCMA portal reported.
title: ICCIMA holds conference on economic security

description: TEHRAN- The value of Iran’s non-oil trade with its neighboring countries increased 23 percent in the first seven months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-October 21), as compared to the same period of time in the past year, the head of the Islamic Republic of Iran Customs Administration (IRICA) announced.
title: Non-oil trade with neighbors up 23% in 7 months on year

description: TEHRAN – Based on the latest data released by the Iranian Ports and Maritime Organization (PMO), some 135,555,142 tons of goods were loaded and unloaded at the country’s ports in the first seven months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20- October 21).
title: Over 135m tons of goods loaded, unloaded at Iranian ports in 7 months

description: TEHRAN – Iranian rower Kia Skandani was banned for seven years after he was tested positive for the banned substance meldonium.
title: Iranian rower banned for seven years for doping

description: TEHRAN - Iran’s freestyle wrestlers Amirhossein Firouzpour and Amirreza Masoumi won two gold medals in the 2024 U23 World Championships.
title: Iranian freestylers win two golds at 2024 U23 World Championships
